# Mail templates and delivery

## Template rules

- Place templates in `src/modules/mail/templates/*.hbs`.
- Use consistent context keys (`name`, `code`, `temporaryPassword`, etc.).
- Always use the filename without `.hbs` as the template id.

## Styling rules

All templates in `src/modules/mail/templates/*.hbs` MUST follow the same shadcn-inspired style. No loose, unstyled HTML. Match visually with the existing templates (`activation-code`, `reset-password`, `password-changed`, `email-change-confirmation`, `email-change-notice`, `new-user-credentials`, `support-contact`, `welcome`).

- Inline CSS only — no Tailwind, no external stylesheets, no helpers beyond plain Handlebars placeholders.
- Body wrapper: `background-color: #f8fafc`, `padding: 24px 12px`, Inter font stack, `color: #0f172a`, `line-height: 1.6`.
- Card via `<table role="presentation">` wrappers: `max-width: 560px`, white background, `border: 1px solid #e2e8f0`, `border-radius: 12px`, `overflow: hidden`.
- Header row: `padding: 28px 28px 12px 28px;` with a small uppercase label (`font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #64748b`) above an `h1` of `font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; color: #0f172a`.
- Body copy: `font-size: 15px; color: #334155`, opening with a `Hi {{name}},` or `Hello {{name}},` greeting.
- Buttons: `background-color: #0f172a`, white text, `border-radius: 8px`, `padding: 10px 16px` (or `12px 18px`), `font-weight: 600`.
- Code/secret blocks: light `#f8fafc` panel with `#e2e8f0` (or dashed `#cbd5e1`) border, `border-radius: 10px`, monospace font (`ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, ...`), uppercase label above the value.
- Notice/alert blocks:
  - warning → `#fff7ed` + `#fed7aa` + `#9a3412`;
  - security alert → `#fff1f2` + `#fecdd3` + `#9f1239`.
- Footer: muted `color: #64748b`, divider via `padding-top: 14px; border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0`, ending with "This is an automated message. Please do not reply.".
- Keep text contrast high and use tables as layout wrappers for broad email-client support.

## Delivery rules

- Send mail via the queue, not directly from feature services.
- Use `QueueService.addMailJob(MAIL_JOB_SEND, payload)` as the standard.
- The payload contains at minimum: `to`, `subject`, `template`, `context`.

## Rendering rules

- Keep rendering centralised in `MailService`.
- Use `MailService.renderTemplate()` as the only place for compile logic.
- Keep template business logic minimal; limit it to simple placeholders.

## Build rules

- New `.hbs` templates do not need additional configuration as long as they live under `src/**` (asset copy is already configured in `nest-cli.json`).
